      node server/back end technology

      basic commands
      --------------------

      1.create package.json=>npm init
      2.install express npm i express
      install jwt token- npm i json
    
      basic steps
      -------------------
      1.create package json

      2.install express

      3.create index.js file

      4.import express

      5.server app creation using express

      6.setup port number for express

      7.client http req resolving
        syntax:server-app.http-request(pat,callback)

      8.response status cose
      
       1xx=> information
       2xx=> success
       3xx=> redirection
       4xx=> client side error
       5xx=> server side error
      
      9.jwt token-uer validation
       
        9.1 token generation -sign() to generate
        9.2 token verify -verify()

      10.middleware -
       10.1 application specific=>entair application
       10.2 router specific=>only want some api

      11.mong0 db connection
       11.1 install mongoose
       11.2 create db.js file
       11.3 import mongoose in db.js
       11.4 state connection string using mongoose
       11.5 create model or collection
       11.6 export model

      12.asynchronou function resolving-promise
       12.1 resolved state 
